The film Suspiria is a fantasy-thriller/ horror that tells a story about a young woman who enrols in a dance academy in Berlin Germany troubled by strange occurrences. The mysterious disappearances of students help them realise that the school may possess a dark secret that could kill them all. This film is a remake of Suspiria made in 1978. The film had its world premiere on 1 September at The Venice international Film Festival, would have a limited release in New York and Los Angeles on 26 October 2018 and open widely on 2 November 2018. It features Dakota Johnson, Tilda Swinton, Chloe Grace Moretz amongst others. The film is somewhat horrific and graphic for some viewers and not for the faint-hearted.